A health worker prepares to conduct a COVID-19 coronavirus molecular test. AFP/Luca Sola JOHANNESBURG - The cumulative number of detected infections in South Africa is now at 746,945. The Health Department has also reported 106 new deaths, taking the death toll to almost 20,153. READ: 106 new COVID-19 deaths recorded Of the 77 deaths reported, 16 were recorded in the past 48 hours. Eastern Cape had the highest number of deaths, with 11 reported. The recovery rate remains at 92.7-percent. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.